{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-m3-exit-confirmed.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — Milestone 3 Exit Confirmed\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer`\n- bounded target: run a weekly-report actionability exit review to decide whether this guidance surface is now concrete enough to move on to the next Milestone 3 gap\n\n## Completed\n\n- Reviewed Milestone 3 against the `ROADMAP.md` exit criteria after the weekly `Next action` cue landed\n- Confirmed that report persistence/reload fallback, topic-map/thread-list linkage, and weekly guidance actionability now each have a concrete UI path\n- Marked Milestone 3 complete in the active plan\n- Promoted Milestone 4 to active status and narrowed the next slice to an operational audit of background continue and status surfaces\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- No code changes were made in this review slice\n- No packaging run was needed because behavior did not change\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat Milestone 3 as sufficiently closed for now instead of continuing to polish weekly guidance wording\n- Start Milestone 4 with an audit slice rather than guessing the first operational fix\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md` using `ROADMAP.md` as the anchor. Milestone 3 is complete; move to Milestone 4. Do one minimal slice only: audit the current background continue and status surfaces to identify the first smallest operational reliability gap, then update the active plan, append a new evolution note, and sync to `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
